# UI5 Design System Rules

This project uses **SAP UI5 Web Components** exclusively. The UI5 design system has been indexed and is available for reference.

## Core Rules

### 1. Use UI5 Components Only
- ✅ All interactive UI must use `<ui5-*>` components from the indexed design system
- ✅ Use semantic HTML for layout only (`<div>`, `<span>`, `<p>`, `<section>`)
- ❌ Never use other UI frameworks (Material, Bootstrap, etc.)
- ❌ Never use plain interactive HTML (`<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>`)

### 2. Import Every Component
- Import components individually in `app.module.ts`: `import '@ui5/webcomponents/dist/Button';`
- Add `CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA` to the module's `schemas` array
- Never import entire packages

### 3. Configure Theme
- Set theme in `app.module.ts`: `setTheme('sap_horizon');`
- Add `xx-wc-no-conflict` event config to `index.html`

### 4. Angular Integration
- Access components via `@ViewChild` with `ElementRef`
- UI5 events provide data in `event.detail`
- Call methods via `nativeElement`: `this.dialog.nativeElement.show()`

## Quick Reference

**Valid Approach:**

<ui5-button design="Emphasized" (click)="submit()">Submit</ui5-button>
<ui5-input placeholder="Name" (input)="onChange($event)"></ui5-input>
```

**Invalid Approach:**
```html
<button (click)="submit()">Submit</button> <!-- ❌ Plain HTML -->
<mat-button>Submit</mat-button> <!-- ❌ Other framework -->
```

## Resources
- Components: https://ui5.github.io/webcomponents/
- Design System: https://www.sap.com/design-system/fiori-design-web/
- Icons: https://ui5.github.io/webcomponents/icons/

Refer to `.builder/rules/*.mdc` for detailed enforcement rules.
